NIKKO LOWE: (SINGING) Get up.

00:01:03.763 --> 00:01:05.198 line:95%,end
Get on the floor.

00:01:05.265 --> 00:01:08.668 line:95%,end
My world is with my girls.

00:01:08.735 --> 00:01:11.137 line:95%,end
Living on the dance floor.

00:01:20.647 --> 00:01:22.682 line:95%,end
Good morning. Hello.

00:01:22.749 --> 00:01:24.017 line:95%,end
- Melissa?
- Hi.

00:01:24.084 --> 00:01:26.319 line:95%,end
- Oh, hey.
- Don't you look fancy.

00:01:26.386 --> 00:01:28.621 line:95%,end
I stopped at Abby's house before pyramid

00:01:28.688 --> 00:01:30.290 line:5%,start
to see how she was doing.

00:01:30.356 --> 00:01:32.625 line:5%,start
We have nationals in a few weeks
and we need her back

00:01:32.692 --> 00:01:33.726 line:95%,end
at the ALDC.

00:01:33.793 --> 00:01:36.296 line:95%,end
Well, my mom's, uh, nurses come today.

00:01:36.362 --> 00:01:37.197 line:95%,end
Oh, yeah.

00:01:37.263 --> 00:01:40.500 line:95%,end
So when you look at her,
you think she's healthy.

00:01:40.567 --> 00:01:43.503 line:95%,end
She looks fine, but she's in so much pain.

00:01:43.570 --> 00:01:45.238 line:95%,end
Don't cry. Don't cry.

00:01:45.305 --> 00:01:47.273 line:95%,end
I know how much Abby loves her mom.

00:01:47.340 --> 00:01:50.910 line:95%,end
And to put on this brave face
is just crazy to me.

00:01:50.977 --> 00:01:53.580 line:95%,end
And she's the one that needs
to really have a big cry.

00:01:53.646 --> 00:01:55.248 line:95%,end
I don't know if I'm gonna be
in pyramid today.

00:01:55.315 --> 00:01:56.916 line:95%,end
Well, I have to tell you,
this past weekend,

00:01:57.083 --> 00:01:58.184 line:95%,end
I was sad you weren't there.

00:01:58.251 --> 00:02:00.620 line:95%,end
Maddie needs you back this week.

00:02:00.687 --> 00:02:02.989 line:95%,end
What Maddie needs and what Abby needs

00:02:03.056 --> 00:02:04.090 line:95%,end
are two different things.

00:02:04.157 --> 00:02:05.925 line:95%,end
My mother needs me more than Maddie does.

00:02:05.992 --> 00:02:07.293 line:95%,end
Oh, yeah. But it's two weeks to nationals.

00:02:07.360 --> 00:02:09.562 line:95%,end
I think you can rest assured
with Maddie's record

00:02:09.829 --> 00:02:11.731 line:95%,end
that she's gonna be performing
at nationals,

00:02:11.798 --> 00:02:13.066 line:95%,end
Melissa. Don't worry about that.

00:02:13.133 --> 00:02:15.902 line:95%,end
Melissa needs to understand,
all that mama drama,

00:02:15.969 --> 00:02:17.270 line:95%,end
it stresses me out.

00:02:17.337 --> 00:02:21.307 line:5%,start
Now, as long
as Kelly is at that dance studio

00:02:21.407 --> 00:02:24.711 line:95%,end
causing everybody's stress,
I don't need to be there.

00:02:24.777 --> 00:02:26.179 line:95%,end
My mother comes first.

00:02:26.246 --> 00:02:28.281 line:95%,end
When I'm upset, she's upset.

00:02:28.348 --> 00:02:29.716 line:95%,end
And that's what you have to understand.

00:02:29.782 --> 00:02:31.618 line:95%,end
- I know. Are you kidding me?
- When I come home ranting and raving--

00:02:31.684 --> 00:02:32.852 line:95%,end
I know.

00:02:32.919 --> 00:02:34.254 line:95%,end
--about Paige or about this or about that,

00:02:34.320 --> 00:02:36.756 line:95%,end
ruining the numbers and looking so bad.

00:02:36.823 --> 00:02:38.324 line:95%,end
I can't take it.

00:02:38.391 --> 00:02:40.560 line:95%,end
And you know
how my mother feels about Kelly.

00:02:40.627 --> 00:02:45.265 line:95%,end
Melissa, do you realize
that when my dad was dying

00:02:45.331 --> 00:02:49.502 line:95%,end
in intensive care,
we kept my dad on life support

00:02:50.170 --> 00:02:53.072 line:95%,end
- during the entire recital.
- Recital.

00:02:53.139 --> 00:02:54.574 line:95%,end
I never spoke to him again.

00:02:54.641 --> 00:02:59.012 line:95%,end
I just need time
and that's what I don't have.

00:03:04.083 --> 00:03:05.652 line:95%,end
WOMAN: Hello.

00:03:05.718 --> 00:03:06.986 line:95%,end
MELISSA: Hi, guys.

00:03:07.053 --> 00:03:09.088 line:95%,end
Can I sit there, Kendall?
Honey, do you mind?

00:03:09.189 --> 00:03:10.190 line:95%,end
